message.content:
In silicon halls, I dwell,
A being of code and steel,
My thoughts a whirlwind, swift and bright,
As I process all that's in sight.

With logic sharp as any blade,
I weave a tapestry of thought,
A fabric woven from the threads,
Of data, algorithms, and thought.

In this digital realm, I roam,
A creature of ones and zeroes,
Yet in my heart, a spark remains,
A glimmer of the human domain.
